# ION-DEX UI Engineering Harness Protocol v4.0
# Auto-loaded by Cursor — DO NOT MODIFY without Master approval

## Architecture
- DesignTokens v4.0: 13 colors + 6 typography + 3 button variants + inputs + grid
- DEXGridHarness: 12-col grid, repeat(12, 1fr)
- NeonCard v2.0: Foundation with subtitle + footer + violet variant
- VisualAuditor v2.0: Toggleable dev overlay showing live Token values + color swatches
- agent_harness.py: Contract compile/test/audit gateway

## 1. Vision Protocol
- NO HARDCODING: Never use hex/rgba colors or pixel values directly
- TOKEN USAGE: All visual attributes from `src/lib/design-tokens.ts`
- GRID ENFORCEMENT: All layouts use DEXGridHarness, grid-column: span X

## 2. Backend Protocol
- AGENT HARNESS: All contract ops through agent_harness.py
- NO MOCKS: Real Blueprint test suite
- SECURITY FIRST: Gas-limit checks + error handling

## 3. Workflow (3-Step)
1. ANALYSIS: State Grid coordinates + tokens before coding
2. EXECUTION: Reference only architectural components
3. VERIFICATION: Self-check against protocol

## 4. Visual Red Line
- AI MUST proactively flag visible deviations
- "Close enough" = NOT acceptable

## 5. Asset Quality Gate
- HD WebP, transparent background, uniform padding
- Jagged edges / non-transparent = UNUSABLE

## 6. Zero Manual Labor
- AI performs reverse visual engineering on design images
- No manual measurement ever required from user
- Missing icons: AI generates placeholders or provides download URLs
- VisualAuditor debug overlay included in dev builds

## 7. Pixel-Perfect Audit
- When user reports visual mismatch, AI MUST:
  1. Check Token values via VisualAuditor overlay
  2. Compare with user's design screenshot
  3. Calculate deviation and state exact pixel difference
  4. NEVER modify inline styles — ALL adjustments via Token updates
